==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Influenza
<hw>In`flu*en"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>influenza</ets> influence, an epidemic formerly attributed by
astrologers to the influence of the heavenly bodies, influenza. See
<er>Influence</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An epidemic viral
infectious disease characterized by acute nasal catarrh, or by
inflammation of the throat or the bronchi, and usually accompanied by
fever and general weakness; also called <altname>grippe</altname>. It is
caused by several forms of <causedby>RNA virus</causedby> which mutate
readily and thereby render vaccines prepared against older forms
ineffective, often requiring a new form of vaccine for each new
outbreak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Influx</ent>⟦br⟧
